ss works differently on either side of the color line. She contends that the allusiveness and incompleteness of Baldwin's essays sustains the tension between general claims about American racial history and the singularity of individual experiences. The Evidence of Things Not Said establishes Baldwin's contributions to democratic theory and situates him as an indispensable voice in contemporary debates about racial injustice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAfrican Americans in literature. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and government. 0aPolitical fiction, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturezUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 4aPhilosophy. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172081940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501720819423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501720819.jpg  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2010  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK